        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; color: var(--color-brand);">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 12 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 3 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1 1.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0 1 12 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 1.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 21 12Z" />
        </svg>
        Suggested Clickbait YouTube Titles
      </h3>

      <div class="usernames-grid" id="generated-titles-container">
        <!-- Results dynamic content goes here -->
      </div>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <button type="button" id="generate-more-btn" class="calc-btn" style="max-width: 200px; padding: 0 1.5rem;">Generate More</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>YouTube Clickbait Title Generator: Boost Click-Through Rates (CTR)</h2>
    <div style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5;">
        📏 <strong>Want to make sure your title fits mobile screens perfectly?</strong> Check title character limits with our free <a href="/tools/youtube-title-length-checker" style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;">YouTube Title Length Checker</a> to prevent mobile title cropping.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      In YouTube content creation, your title and thumbnail are the two most critical factors determining your video's Click-Through Rate (CTR). Even if your video features Hollywood-grade production value, no one will watch it if your title fails to spark curiosity in recommendation feeds. YouTube handles millions of uploads daily, and standing out requires leveraging psychological curiosity gaps, emotional triggers, and urgency phrasing. Our free <strong>YouTube clickbait title generator</strong> helps creators, vloggers, and digital marketers craft high-converting, attention-grabbing titles that entice viewers to click while maintaining content honesty.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      Generating high-CTR clickbait YouTube titles in real-time is straightforward. Follow these simple steps:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Video Topic or Seed Concept:</strong> Enter your core video concept or main keyword (e.g. iPhone 16, day in the life, crypto crash).</li>
      <li><strong>Clickbait Vibe:</strong> Select an emotional style filter (Extreme Curiosity & Shock, Dramatic & Urgent, Secret & Hidden Knowledge, Challenge & Impossible, or High-Energy & Reaction).</li>
      <li><strong>Target Niche:</strong> Choose your channel's niche (Tech & Gadgets, Gaming, Vlogs, Finance, or General YouTube).</li>
      <li><strong>Formatting Add-ons:</strong> Select toggles to include ALL CAPS power words, emojis, or bracket hooks.</li>
      <li><strong>Generate List:</strong> Click <strong>Generate Clickbait Titles</strong> to view 15 custom options complete with character count badges.</li>
      <li><strong>Preview & Copy:</strong> Click any title card to preview how it looks inside a live YouTube mobile video card, and copy it to your clipboard. Click <strong>Generate More</strong> to append 5 more options.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is YouTube Clickbait Title Generator</h3>
    <p>
      A <strong>YouTube clickbait title generator</strong> is an advanced video marketing tool engineered to create compelling, curiosity-driven titles by combining your seed topic with high-converting power words, emotional hooks, and psychological curiosity gaps.
    </p>
    <p>
      Using a dedicated <strong>clickbait generator for YouTube</strong> helps you balance CTR optimization with audience retention:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>The Curiosity Gap:</strong> Creating a knowledge gap between what the viewer knows and what they want to know (e.g. <i>"I Tried Working Out Like The Rock for 30 Days... (THIS HAPPENED)"</i>).</li>
      <li><strong>Ethical Clickbait vs. Misleading Clickbait:</strong> Ethical clickbait uses high-energy phrasing to highlight the most exciting aspect of a video. Misleading clickbait makes promises the video fails to deliver, leading to high bounce rates.</li>
      <li><strong>SEO Keyword Balance:</strong> Blending curiosity hooks with search keywords so your video ranks in YouTube search results while capturing clicks in recommendation feeds. Discover target keywords with our <a href="/tools/youtube-keyword-generator">YouTube Keyword Generator</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      The generator processes your seed concept through proven YouTube title formulas:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Power Word Insertion:</strong> Integrates high-converting trigger words (such as 'SECRET', 'NEVER', 'WARNING', 'DONT', or 'SHOCKING') to command visual attention in feeds.</li>
      <li><strong>Bracket & Hook Structuring:</strong> Encloses key emotional teasers inside brackets or parentheses—a proven technique used by top YouTubers to increase CTR by up to 20%.</li>
      <li><strong>Character Count Trimming:</strong> Trims titles to optimal length (between 50 and 70 characters) so your full hook remains visible on mobile screens. Generate tags for your upload with our <a href="/tools/youtube-tag-generator">YouTube Tag Generator</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How To Use</h3>
    <p>
      Using our generator is intuitive. Simply type your video concept into the input field, pick your preferred clickbait vibe, and click generate. Clicking any title card automatically updates the live mobile video mockup card, giving you an exact visual preview of how your title will appear in YouTube's mobile home feed before publishing.
    </p>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>
      This generator is designed for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>YouTubers & Content Creators:</strong> Looking to boost click-through rates on new uploads or revive underperforming videos.</li>
      <li><strong>Vloggers & Influencers:</strong> Crafting high-energy storytelling titles that spark curiosity.</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Marketers & Video Agencies:</strong> Optimizing video campaign titles for maximum viewer reach.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

